\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Across individual fields, the same
ordering pattern is frequently observed, with OpenAI's model producing
the highest scores across most academic fields, followed by Gemini, then
Llama-4 Maverick, with Claude Opus and Grok trailing. For example, in
computer science, the reported scores were OpenAI = 71.1, Gemini = 65.5,
Llama-4 Maverick = 56.1, Claude = 43.3, and Grok = 40.1. In
business-management-and-accounting, reported scores were OpenAI = 72.3,
Gemini = 65.5, Llama-4 Maverick = 62.4, Claude = 52.8, and Grok = 39.6.
These results demonstrate measurable between-model differences in both
overall and domain-specific performance.}

 A side-by-side comparison of
eight representative fields is presented in
Figure~\ref{fig:grouped-bars}, and the per-model range between each
model's strongest and weakest disciplinary performance is shown in
Figure~\ref{fig:strength-weakness}, which highlights both the breadth
of within-model variability and the recurring rank ordering across
domains.

