\hypertarget{introduction-1}{%
\subsection*{Introduction}\label{introduction-1}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Introduction}

\hypertarget{the-problem-addressed-in-this-study-is-that-contemporary-large-language-models-llms-demonstrate-uneven-and-insufficiently-quantified-knowledge-across-the-26-major-academic-fields.-at-the-same-time-stakeholders-lack-empirically-validated-field-level-rankings-to-guide-adoption-governance-and-risk-management-decisions.-although-llms-are-often-characterized-as-general-purpose-systems-prior-research-and-benchmark-reporting-practices-obscure-meaningful-variation-in-domain-specific-performance.}{%
\section*{The problem addressed in this study is that contemporary large
language models (LLMs) demonstrate uneven and insufficiently quantified
knowledge across the 26 major academic fields. At the same time,
stakeholders lack empirically validated, field-level rankings to guide
adoption, governance, and risk management decisions. Although LLMs are
often characterized as general-purpose systems, prior research and
benchmark reporting practices obscure meaningful variation in
domain-specific
performance.}\label{the-problem-addressed-in-this-study-is-that-contemporary-large-language-models-llms-demonstrate-uneven-and-insufficiently-quantified-knowledge-across-the-26-major-academic-fields.-at-the-same-time-stakeholders-lack-empirically-validated-field-level-rankings-to-guide-adoption-governance-and-risk-management-decisions.-although-llms-are-often-characterized-as-general-purpose-systems-prior-research-and-benchmark-reporting-practices-obscure-meaningful-variation-in-domain-specific-performance.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{The problem addressed in this study is
that contemporary large language models (LLMs) demonstrate uneven and
insufficiently quantified knowledge across the 26 major academic fields.
At the same time, stakeholders lack empirically validated, field-level
rankings to guide adoption, governance, and risk management decisions.
Although LLMs are often characterized as general-purpose systems, prior
research and benchmark reporting practices obscure meaningful variation
in domain-specific performance.}

\hypertarget{the-purpose-of-this-quantitative-comparative-benchmarking-study-was-to-evaluate-and-rank-leading-llms-across-26-academic-fields-using-a-standardized-testing-framework-and-statistical-analysis.-a-quasi-experimental-design-was-employed-administering-1000-multiple-choice-items-per-field-to-each-model-and-aggregating-results-into-overall-and-field-level-performance-scores.-chapter-4-presented-the-pilot-study-outcomes-and-the-primary-evaluation-results-demonstrating-apparent-between-model-differences-and-substantial-variability-across-academic-domains.}{%
\section*{The purpose of this quantitative, comparative benchmarking
study was to evaluate and rank leading LLMs across 26 academic fields
using a standardized testing framework and statistical analysis. A
quasi-experimental design was employed, administering 1,000
multiple-choice items per field to each model and aggregating results
into overall and field-level performance scores. Chapter 4 presented the
pilot study outcomes and the primary evaluation results, demonstrating
apparent between-model differences and substantial variability across
academic
domains.}\label{the-purpose-of-this-quantitative-comparative-benchmarking-study-was-to-evaluate-and-rank-leading-llms-across-26-academic-fields-using-a-standardized-testing-framework-and-statistical-analysis.-a-quasi-experimental-design-was-employed-administering-1000-multiple-choice-items-per-field-to-each-model-and-aggregating-results-into-overall-and-field-level-performance-scores.-chapter-4-presented-the-pilot-study-outcomes-and-the-primary-evaluation-results-demonstrating-apparent-between-model-differences-and-substantial-variability-across-academic-domains.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{The purpose of this quantitative,
comparative benchmarking study was to evaluate and rank leading LLMs
across 26 academic fields using a standardized testing framework and
statistical analysis. A quasi-experimental design was employed,
administering 1,000 multiple-choice items per field to each model and
aggregating results into overall and field-level performance scores.
Chapter 4 presented the pilot study outcomes and the primary evaluation
results, demonstrating apparent between-model differences and
substantial variability across academic domains.}

\hypertarget{this-chapter-interprets-the-results-in-relation-to-the-research-questions-discusses-the-studys-limitations-and-outlines-the-implications-contributions-and-recommendations-for-future-research.-together-these-sections-contextualize-the-findings-within-the-existing-literature-and-highlight-their-significance-for-both-theory-and-practice.}{%
\section*{This chapter interprets the results in relation to the
research questions, discusses the study\textquotesingle s limitations,
and outlines the implications, contributions, and recommendations for
future research. Together, these sections contextualize the findings
within the existing literature and highlight their significance for both
theory and
practice.}\label{this-chapter-interprets-the-results-in-relation-to-the-research-questions-discusses-the-studys-limitations-and-outlines-the-implications-contributions-and-recommendations-for-future-research.-together-these-sections-contextualize-the-findings-within-the-existing-literature-and-highlight-their-significance-for-both-theory-and-practice.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{This chapter interprets the results in
relation to the research questions, discusses the
study\textquotesingle s limitations, and outlines the implications,
contributions, and recommendations for future research. Together, these
sections contextualize the findings within the existing literature and
highlight their significance for both theory and practice.}

\hypertarget{limitations}{%
\section*{Limitations}\label{limitations}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Limitations}

\hypertarget{several-limitations-should-be-considered-when-interpreting-the-findings-of-this-study.-first-the-evaluation-relied-on-multiple-choice-questions-as-the-primary-instrument-of-measurement.-while-this-format-enables-large-scale-standardized-comparison-across-fields-it-may-underrepresent-higher-order-reasoning-creative-synthesis-and-open-ended-problem-solving-abilities-that-are-also-relevant-to-academic-expertise.}{%
\section*{Several limitations should be considered when interpreting the
findings of this study. First, the evaluation relied on multiple-choice
questions as the primary instrument of measurement. While this format
enables large-scale, standardized comparison across fields, it may
underrepresent higher-order reasoning, creative synthesis, and
open-ended problem-solving abilities that are also relevant to academic
expertise.}\label{several-limitations-should-be-considered-when-interpreting-the-findings-of-this-study.-first-the-evaluation-relied-on-multiple-choice-questions-as-the-primary-instrument-of-measurement.-while-this-format-enables-large-scale-standardized-comparison-across-fields-it-may-underrepresent-higher-order-reasoning-creative-synthesis-and-open-ended-problem-solving-abilities-that-are-also-relevant-to-academic-expertise.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Several limitations should be considered
when interpreting the findings of this study. First, the evaluation
relied on multiple-choice questions as the primary instrument of
measurement. While this format enables large-scale, standardized
comparison across fields, it may underrepresent higher-order reasoning,
creative synthesis, and open-ended problem-solving abilities that are
also relevant to academic expertise.}

\hypertarget{second-the-study-evaluated-models-at-a-fixed-point-in-time.-llms-are-rapidly-evolving-and-performance-characteristics-may-change-as-models-are-updated-fine-tuned-or-replaced.-consequently-the-rankings-presented-here-should-be-interpreted-as-a-snapshot-rather-than-a-permanent-ordering-of-model-capabilities.}{%
\section*{Second, the study evaluated models at a fixed point in time.
LLMs are rapidly evolving, and performance characteristics may change as
models are updated, fine-tuned, or replaced. Consequently, the rankings
presented here should be interpreted as a snapshot rather than a
permanent ordering of model
capabilities.}\label{second-the-study-evaluated-models-at-a-fixed-point-in-time.-llms-are-rapidly-evolving-and-performance-characteristics-may-change-as-models-are-updated-fine-tuned-or-replaced.-consequently-the-rankings-presented-here-should-be-interpreted-as-a-snapshot-rather-than-a-permanent-ordering-of-model-capabilities.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Second, the study evaluated models at a
fixed point in time. LLMs are rapidly evolving, and performance
characteristics may change as models are updated, fine-tuned, or
replaced. Consequently, the rankings presented here should be
interpreted as a snapshot rather than a permanent ordering of model
capabilities.}

\hypertarget{third-although-care-was-taken-to-standardize-prompts-and-scoring-differences-in-model-architectures-training-data-and-alignment-strategies-may-introduce-latent-biases-that-are-difficult-to-isolate-fully.-some-models-also-exhibited-failure-states-or-near-zero-outputs-which-may-reflect-incompatibilities-with-the-evaluation-configuration-rather-than-the-actual-absence-of-knowledge.}{%
\section*{Third, although care was taken to standardize prompts and
scoring, differences in model architectures, training data, and
alignment strategies may introduce latent biases that are difficult to
isolate fully. Some models also exhibited failure states or near-zero
outputs, which may reflect incompatibilities with the evaluation
configuration rather than the actual absence of
knowledge.}\label{third-although-care-was-taken-to-standardize-prompts-and-scoring-differences-in-model-architectures-training-data-and-alignment-strategies-may-introduce-latent-biases-that-are-difficult-to-isolate-fully.-some-models-also-exhibited-failure-states-or-near-zero-outputs-which-may-reflect-incompatibilities-with-the-evaluation-configuration-rather-than-the-actual-absence-of-knowledge.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Third, although care was taken to
standardize prompts and scoring, differences in model architectures,
training data, and alignment strategies may introduce latent biases that
are difficult to isolate fully. Some models also exhibited failure
states or near-zero outputs, which may reflect incompatibilities with
the evaluation configuration rather than the actual absence of
knowledge.}

\hypertarget{finally-the-study-focused-on-english-language-academic-content-aligned-with-the-scopus-field-taxonomy.-results-may-not-generalize-directly-to-non-english-contexts-interdisciplinary-tasks-or-professional-applications-that-extend-beyond-academic-knowledge-assessment.}{%
\section*{Finally, the study focused on English-language academic
content aligned with the Scopus field taxonomy. Results may not
generalize directly to non-English contexts, interdisciplinary tasks, or
professional applications that extend beyond academic knowledge
assessment.}\label{finally-the-study-focused-on-english-language-academic-content-aligned-with-the-scopus-field-taxonomy.-results-may-not-generalize-directly-to-non-english-contexts-interdisciplinary-tasks-or-professional-applications-that-extend-beyond-academic-knowledge-assessment.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Finally, the study focused on
English-language academic content aligned with the Scopus field
taxonomy. Results may not generalize directly to non-English contexts,
interdisciplinary tasks, or professional applications that extend beyond
academic knowledge assessment.}

\hypertarget{despite-these-limitations-the-study-provides-a-robust-and-replicable-framework-for-comparing-llm-knowledge-across-a-broad-range-of-disciplines-thereby-addressing-a-significant-gap-in-current-benchmarking-practices.}{%
\section*{Despite these limitations, the study provides a robust and
replicable framework for comparing LLM knowledge across a broad range of
disciplines, thereby addressing a significant gap in current
benchmarking
practices.}\label{despite-these-limitations-the-study-provides-a-robust-and-replicable-framework-for-comparing-llm-knowledge-across-a-broad-range-of-disciplines-thereby-addressing-a-significant-gap-in-current-benchmarking-practices.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Despite these limitations, the study
provides a robust and replicable framework for comparing LLM knowledge
across a broad range of disciplines, thereby addressing a significant
gap in current benchmarking practices.}

\hypertarget{findings-and-interpretations}{%
\subsection*{Findings and
Interpretations}\label{findings-and-interpretations}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Findings and Interpretations}

\hypertarget{research-question-1}{%
\subsubsection*{Research Question 1}\label{research-question-1}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsubsection}{Research Question 1}

\hypertarget{rq1-does-any-current-large-language-model-llm-exhibit-statistically-uniform-performance-across-the-26-academic-fields-under-study}{%
\section*{\texorpdfstring{RQ1: \emph{Does any current large-language
model (LLM) exhibit statistically uniform performance across the 26
academic fields under
study?}}{RQ1: Does any current large-language model (LLM) exhibit statistically uniform performance across the 26 academic fields under study?}}\label{rq1-does-any-current-large-language-model-llm-exhibit-statistically-uniform-performance-across-the-26-academic-fields-under-study}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{RQ1: \emph{Does any current
large-language model (LLM) exhibit statistically uniform performance
across the 26 academic fields under study?}}

\hypertarget{finding}{%
\section*{Finding}\label{finding}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Finding}

\hypertarget{no-evaluated-model-demonstrated-uniform-performance-across-all-26-academic-fields.}{%
\section*{No evaluated model demonstrated uniform performance across all
26 academic
fields.}\label{no-evaluated-model-demonstrated-uniform-performance-across-all-26-academic-fields.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{No evaluated model demonstrated uniform
performance across all 26 academic fields.}

\hypertarget{interpretation}{%
\section*{Interpretation}\label{interpretation}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Interpretation}

\hypertarget{analysis-of-field-level-scores-revealed-consistent-variability-within-each-models-performance-profile.-even-the-highest-performing-models-exhibited-meaningful-differences-across-fields-such-as-economics-materials-science-medicine-and-pharmacology.-these-results-indicate-that-general-intelligence-claims-mask-important-domain-specific-strengths-and-weaknesses.-uniform-performance-across-disciplines-remains-unrealized-in-current-llm-architectures.}{%
\section*{\texorpdfstring{\hfill\break
Analysis of field-level scores revealed consistent variability within
each model's performance profile. Even the highest-performing models
exhibited meaningful differences across fields such as economics,
materials science, medicine, and pharmacology. These results indicate
that ``general intelligence'' claims mask important domain-specific
strengths and weaknesses. Uniform performance across disciplines remains
unrealized in current LLM
architectures.}{ Analysis of field-level scores revealed consistent variability within each model's performance profile. Even the highest-performing models exhibited meaningful differences across fields such as economics, materials science, medicine, and pharmacology. These results indicate that ``general intelligence'' claims mask important domain-specific strengths and weaknesses. Uniform performance across disciplines remains unrealized in current LLM architectures.}}\label{analysis-of-field-level-scores-revealed-consistent-variability-within-each-models-performance-profile.-even-the-highest-performing-models-exhibited-meaningful-differences-across-fields-such-as-economics-materials-science-medicine-and-pharmacology.-these-results-indicate-that-general-intelligence-claims-mask-important-domain-specific-strengths-and-weaknesses.-uniform-performance-across-disciplines-remains-unrealized-in-current-llm-architectures.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{\hfill\break
Analysis of field-level scores revealed consistent variability within
each model's performance profile. Even the highest-performing models
exhibited meaningful differences across fields such as economics,
materials science, medicine, and pharmacology. These results indicate
that ``general intelligence'' claims mask important domain-specific
strengths and weaknesses. Uniform performance across disciplines remains
unrealized in current LLM architectures.}

