\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Yes. Statistically and practically
significant differences in mean performance were observed between
models.}

\hypertarget{interpretation-1}{%
\section*{Interpretation}\label{interpretation-1}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Interpretation}

\hypertarget{the-primary-evaluation-showed-a-clear-ordering-of-overall-performance-with-openais-model-achieving-the-highest-aggregate-score-followed-by-gemini-llama-based-models-and-other-evaluated-systems.-this-ordering-persisted-across-many-individual-fields-though-relative-gaps-widened-or-narrowed-depending-on-disciplinary-complexity.-these-findings-confirm-that-model-choice-materially-affects-expected-performance-in-academic-contexts-and-that-not-all-frontier-models-are-interchangeable-for-domain-specific-tasks.}{%
\section*{\texorpdfstring{ The primary evaluation showed a clear
ordering of overall performance, with OpenAI's model achieving the
highest aggregate score, followed by Gemini, Llama-based models, and
other evaluated systems. This ordering persisted across many individual
fields, though relative gaps widened or narrowed depending on
disciplinary complexity. These findings confirm that model choice
materially affects expected performance in academic contexts and that
not all frontier models are interchangeable for domain-specific
tasks.}{ The primary evaluation showed a clear ordering of overall performance, with OpenAI's model achieving the highest aggregate score, followed by Gemini, Llama-based models, and other evaluated systems. This ordering persisted across many individual fields, though relative gaps widened or narrowed depending on disciplinary complexity. These findings confirm that model choice materially affects expected performance in academic contexts and that not all frontier models are interchangeable for domain-specific tasks.}}\label{the-primary-evaluation-showed-a-clear-ordering-of-overall-performance-with-openais-model-achieving-the-highest-aggregate-score-followed-by-gemini-llama-based-models-and-other-evaluated-systems.-this-ordering-persisted-across-many-individual-fields-though-relative-gaps-widened-or-narrowed-depending-on-disciplinary-complexity.-these-findings-confirm-that-model-choice-materially-affects-expected-performance-in-academic-contexts-and-that-not-all-frontier-models-are-interchangeable-for-domain-specific-tasks.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{ The primary evaluation showed a clear
ordering of overall performance, with OpenAI's model achieving the
highest aggregate score, followed by Gemini, Llama-based models, and
other evaluated systems. This ordering persisted across many individual
fields, though relative gaps widened or narrowed depending on
disciplinary complexity. These findings confirm that model choice
materially affects expected performance in academic contexts and that
not all frontier models are interchangeable for domain-specific tasks.}

\hypertarget{research-question-3}{%
\subsubsection*{Research Question 3}\label{research-question-3}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsubsection}{Research Question 3}

\hypertarget{rq3-do-alternative-validation-methods-yield-different-reliability-or-repeatability-estimates-for-field-level-rankings}{%
\section*{\texorpdfstring{RQ3: \emph{Do alternative validation methods
yield different reliability or repeatability estimates for field-level
rankings?}}{RQ3: Do alternative validation methods yield different reliability or repeatability estimates for field-level rankings?}}\label{rq3-do-alternative-validation-methods-yield-different-reliability-or-repeatability-estimates-for-field-level-rankings}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{RQ3: \emph{Do alternative validation
methods yield different reliability or repeatability estimates for
field-level rankings?}}

\hypertarget{finding-2}{%
\section*{Finding}\label{finding-2}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Finding}

\hypertarget{while-formal-reliability-coefficients-were-not-fully-computed-in-this-phase-pilot-and-primary-results-indicate-stable-performance-patterns-across-repeated-runs.}{%
\section*{While formal reliability coefficients were not fully computed
in this phase, pilot and primary results indicate stable performance
patterns across repeated
runs.}\label{while-formal-reliability-coefficients-were-not-fully-computed-in-this-phase-pilot-and-primary-results-indicate-stable-performance-patterns-across-repeated-runs.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{While formal reliability coefficients
were not fully computed in this phase, pilot and primary results
indicate stable performance patterns across repeated runs.}

\hypertarget{interpretation-2}{%
\section*{Interpretation}\label{interpretation-2}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Interpretation}

\hypertarget{pilot-testing-demonstrated-that-models-with-strong-performance-tended-to-maintain-similar-relative-rankings-across-fields-while-models-exhibiting-failure-states-remained-consistently-low.-this-stability-suggests-that-the-evaluation-framework-produces-repeatable-results-under-controlled-conditions.-however-future-work-should-compute-and-report-formal-reliability-metrics-e.g.-split-half-reliability-bootstrap-confidence-intervals-to-further-strengthen-statistical-validation.}{%
\section*{Pilot testing demonstrated that models with strong performance
tended to maintain similar relative rankings across fields, while models
exhibiting failure states remained consistently low. This stability
suggests that the evaluation framework produces repeatable results under
controlled conditions. However, future work should compute and report
formal reliability metrics (e.g., split-half reliability, bootstrap
confidence intervals) to further strengthen statistical
validation.}\label{pilot-testing-demonstrated-that-models-with-strong-performance-tended-to-maintain-similar-relative-rankings-across-fields-while-models-exhibiting-failure-states-remained-consistently-low.-this-stability-suggests-that-the-evaluation-framework-produces-repeatable-results-under-controlled-conditions.-however-future-work-should-compute-and-report-formal-reliability-metrics-e.g.-split-half-reliability-bootstrap-confidence-intervals-to-further-strengthen-statistical-validation.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Pilot testing demonstrated that models
with strong performance tended to maintain similar relative rankings
across fields, while models exhibiting failure states remained
consistently low. This stability suggests that the evaluation framework
produces repeatable results under controlled conditions. However, future
work should compute and report formal reliability metrics (e.g.,
split-half reliability, bootstrap confidence intervals) to further
strengthen statistical validation.}

\hypertarget{overall-implications-of-the-study}{%
\subsection*{Overall Implications of the
Study}\label{overall-implications-of-the-study}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Overall Implications of the Study}

\hypertarget{the-findings-of-this-study-underscore-the-importance-of-moving-beyond-single-score-benchmarks-when-evaluating-llms.-field-level-performance-variation-has-direct-implications-for-educational-integrity-research-validity-and-organizational-risk.-stakeholders-who-rely-on-aggregate-rankings-may-unknowingly-deploy-models-that-underperform-in-critical-domains-particularly-in-high-stakes-fields-such-as-medicine-pharmacology-and-engineering.}{%
\subsection*{The findings of this study underscore the importance of
moving beyond single-score benchmarks when evaluating LLMs. Field-level
performance variation has direct implications for educational integrity,
research validity, and organizational risk. Stakeholders who rely on
aggregate rankings may unknowingly deploy models that underperform in
critical domains, particularly in high-stakes fields such as medicine,
pharmacology, and
engineering.}\label{the-findings-of-this-study-underscore-the-importance-of-moving-beyond-single-score-benchmarks-when-evaluating-llms.-field-level-performance-variation-has-direct-implications-for-educational-integrity-research-validity-and-organizational-risk.-stakeholders-who-rely-on-aggregate-rankings-may-unknowingly-deploy-models-that-underperform-in-critical-domains-particularly-in-high-stakes-fields-such-as-medicine-pharmacology-and-engineering.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{The findings of this study underscore
the importance of moving beyond single-score benchmarks when evaluating
LLMs. Field-level performance variation has direct implications for
educational integrity, research validity, and organizational risk.
Stakeholders who rely on aggregate rankings may unknowingly deploy
models that underperform in critical domains, particularly in
high-stakes fields such as medicine, pharmacology, and engineering.}

\hypertarget{by-explicitly-answering-the-research-questions-this-study-demonstrates-that-domain-knowledge-in-llms-is-uneven-model-dependent-and-sensitive-to-disciplinary-context.-these-insights-are-essential-for-informed-decision-making-in-academic-enterprise-and-policy-environments.}{%
\section*{By explicitly answering the research questions, this study
demonstrates that domain knowledge in LLMs is uneven, model-dependent,
and sensitive to disciplinary context. These insights are essential for
informed decision-making in academic, enterprise, and policy
environments.}\label{by-explicitly-answering-the-research-questions-this-study-demonstrates-that-domain-knowledge-in-llms-is-uneven-model-dependent-and-sensitive-to-disciplinary-context.-these-insights-are-essential-for-informed-decision-making-in-academic-enterprise-and-policy-environments.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{By explicitly answering the research
questions, this study demonstrates that domain knowledge in LLMs is
uneven, model-dependent, and sensitive to disciplinary context. These
insights are essential for informed decision-making in academic,
enterprise, and policy environments.}

\hypertarget{practical-implications-for-the-field-of-study}{%
\subsection*{Practical Implications for the Field of
Study}\label{practical-implications-for-the-field-of-study}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Practical Implications for the Field
of Study}

\hypertarget{for-practitioners-the-results-suggest-that-model-selection-should-be-domain-aware-rather-than-brand-driven.-institutions-should-evaluate-llms-using-field-specific-benchmarks-aligned-with-their-use-cases-rather-than-assuming-uniform-competence.-in-educational-settings-this-may-inform-the-selection-of-models-appropriate-for-instructional-support-versus-assessment-design.-in-enterprise-and-research-contexts-it-underscores-the-need-for-targeted-validation-before-deployment.}{%
\section*{For practitioners, the results suggest that model selection
should be domain-aware rather than brand-driven. Institutions should
evaluate LLMs using field-specific benchmarks aligned with their use
cases rather than assuming uniform competence. In educational settings,
this may inform the selection of models appropriate for instructional
support versus assessment design. In enterprise and research contexts,
it underscores the need for targeted validation before
deployment.}\label{for-practitioners-the-results-suggest-that-model-selection-should-be-domain-aware-rather-than-brand-driven.-institutions-should-evaluate-llms-using-field-specific-benchmarks-aligned-with-their-use-cases-rather-than-assuming-uniform-competence.-in-educational-settings-this-may-inform-the-selection-of-models-appropriate-for-instructional-support-versus-assessment-design.-in-enterprise-and-research-contexts-it-underscores-the-need-for-targeted-validation-before-deployment.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{For practitioners, the results suggest
that model selection should be domain-aware rather than brand-driven.
Institutions should evaluate LLMs using field-specific benchmarks
aligned with their use cases rather than assuming uniform competence. In
educational settings, this may inform the selection of models
appropriate for instructional support versus assessment design. In
enterprise and research contexts, it underscores the need for targeted
validation before deployment.}

\hypertarget{additionally-the-strong-performance-of-specific-architectures-across-multiple-fields-suggests-that-hybrid-or-ensemble-approachescombining-general-purpose-llms-with-domain-specific-tools-or-fine-tuningmay-offer-a-more-reliable-path-forward-than-reliance-on-a-single-monolithic-model.}{%
\section*{Additionally, the strong performance of specific architectures
across multiple fields suggests that hybrid or ensemble
approaches---combining general-purpose LLMs with domain-specific tools
or fine-tuning---may offer a more reliable path forward than reliance on
a single monolithic
model.}\label{additionally-the-strong-performance-of-specific-architectures-across-multiple-fields-suggests-that-hybrid-or-ensemble-approachescombining-general-purpose-llms-with-domain-specific-tools-or-fine-tuningmay-offer-a-more-reliable-path-forward-than-reliance-on-a-single-monolithic-model.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Additionally, the strong performance of
specific architectures across multiple fields suggests that hybrid or
ensemble approaches---combining general-purpose LLMs with
domain-specific tools or fine-tuning---may offer a more reliable path
forward than reliance on a single monolithic model.}

\hypertarget{contributions-to-the-body-of-knowledge}{%
\subsection*{Contributions to the Body of
Knowledge}\label{contributions-to-the-body-of-knowledge}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Contributions to the Body of
Knowledge}

\hypertarget{this-study-contributes-to-the-literature-in-several-important-ways.-first-it-provides-the-first-comprehensive-field-level-ranking-of-llm-knowledge-across-all-26-academic-disciplines-addressing-a-significant-gap-identified-in-chapter-2.-second-it-operationalizes-a-scalable-evaluation-framework-that-can-be-replicated-extended-and-updated-as-new-models-emerge.-third-the-findings-empirically-demonstrate-that-domain-variance-is-a-fundamental-characteristic-of-current-llms-reinforcing-theoretical-perspectives-from-helm-and-cognitive-load-theory.}{%
\section*{This study contributes to the literature in several important
ways. First, it provides the first comprehensive, field-level ranking of
LLM knowledge across all 26 academic disciplines, addressing a
significant gap identified in Chapter 2. Second, it operationalizes a
scalable evaluation framework that can be replicated, extended, and
updated as new models emerge. Third, the findings empirically
demonstrate that domain variance is a fundamental characteristic of
current LLMs, reinforcing theoretical perspectives from HELM and
cognitive load
theory.}\label{this-study-contributes-to-the-literature-in-several-important-ways.-first-it-provides-the-first-comprehensive-field-level-ranking-of-llm-knowledge-across-all-26-academic-disciplines-addressing-a-significant-gap-identified-in-chapter-2.-second-it-operationalizes-a-scalable-evaluation-framework-that-can-be-replicated-extended-and-updated-as-new-models-emerge.-third-the-findings-empirically-demonstrate-that-domain-variance-is-a-fundamental-characteristic-of-current-llms-reinforcing-theoretical-perspectives-from-helm-and-cognitive-load-theory.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{This study contributes to the literature
in several important ways. First, it provides the first comprehensive,
field-level ranking of LLM knowledge across all 26 academic disciplines,
addressing a significant gap identified in Chapter 2. Second, it
operationalizes a scalable evaluation framework that can be replicated,
extended, and updated as new models emerge. Third, the findings
empirically demonstrate that domain variance is a fundamental
characteristic of current LLMs, reinforcing theoretical perspectives
from HELM and cognitive load theory.}

\hypertarget{in-doing-so-the-study-not-only-fills-an-existing-gap-but-also-creates-new-research-questions-about-how-and-why-specific-architectures-generalize-better-across-domains-than-others.}{%
\section*{In doing so, the study not only fills an existing gap but also
creates new research questions about how and why specific architectures
generalize better across domains than
others.}\label{in-doing-so-the-study-not-only-fills-an-existing-gap-but-also-creates-new-research-questions-about-how-and-why-specific-architectures-generalize-better-across-domains-than-others.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{In doing so, the study not only fills an
existing gap but also creates new research questions about how and why
specific architectures generalize better across domains than others.}

\hypertarget{recommendations-for-future-research}{%
\subsection*{Recommendations for Future
Research}\label{recommendations-for-future-research}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Recommendations for Future Research}

\hypertarget{future-research-should-extend-this-work-in-several-directions.-first-researchers-should-compute-and-report-formal-reliability-and-validity-statistics-to-further-strengthen-confidence-in-field-level-rankings.-second-longitudinal-studies-should-examine-how-model-performance-evolves-as-architectures-and-training-data-change.-third-future-evaluations-should-incorporate-open-ended-and-multimodal-tasks-to-capture-higher-order-reasoning-beyond-multiple-choice-formats.}{%
\section*{Future research should extend this work in several directions.
First, researchers should compute and report formal reliability and
validity statistics to further strengthen confidence in field-level
rankings. Second, longitudinal studies should examine how model
performance evolves as architectures and training data change. Third,
future evaluations should incorporate open-ended and multimodal tasks to
capture higher-order reasoning beyond multiple-choice
formats.}\label{future-research-should-extend-this-work-in-several-directions.-first-researchers-should-compute-and-report-formal-reliability-and-validity-statistics-to-further-strengthen-confidence-in-field-level-rankings.-second-longitudinal-studies-should-examine-how-model-performance-evolves-as-architectures-and-training-data-change.-third-future-evaluations-should-incorporate-open-ended-and-multimodal-tasks-to-capture-higher-order-reasoning-beyond-multiple-choice-formats.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Future research should extend this work
in several directions. First, researchers should compute and report
formal reliability and validity statistics to further strengthen
confidence in field-level rankings. Second, longitudinal studies should
examine how model performance evolves as architectures and training data
change. Third, future evaluations should incorporate open-ended and
multimodal tasks to capture higher-order reasoning beyond
multiple-choice formats.}

\hypertarget{additional-research-could-examine-cross-lingual-performance-interdisciplinary-reasoning-and-the-impact-of-fine-tuning-or-retrieval-augmented-generation-on-domain-specific-accuracy.-finally-applying-this-framework-to-professional-licensure-and-real-world-decision-making-tasks-would-help-bridge-the-gap-between-academic-benchmarking-and-the-governance-of-applied-ai.}{%
\section*{Additional research could examine cross-lingual performance,
interdisciplinary reasoning, and the impact of fine-tuning or
retrieval-augmented generation on domain-specific accuracy. Finally,
applying this framework to professional licensure and real-world
decision-making tasks would help bridge the gap between academic
benchmarking and the governance of applied
AI.}\label{additional-research-could-examine-cross-lingual-performance-interdisciplinary-reasoning-and-the-impact-of-fine-tuning-or-retrieval-augmented-generation-on-domain-specific-accuracy.-finally-applying-this-framework-to-professional-licensure-and-real-world-decision-making-tasks-would-help-bridge-the-gap-between-academic-benchmarking-and-the-governance-of-applied-ai.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Additional research could examine
cross-lingual performance, interdisciplinary reasoning, and the impact
of fine-tuning or retrieval-augmented generation on domain-specific
accuracy. Finally, applying this framework to professional licensure and
real-world decision-making tasks would help bridge the gap between
academic benchmarking and the governance of applied AI.}

\hypertarget{chapter-summary-4}{%
\subsection*{Chapter Summary}\label{chapter-summary-4}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{Chapter Summary}

\hypertarget{this-chapter-interpreted-the-studys-findings-addressed-its-limitations-and-articulated-its-implications-contributions-and-recommendations-for-future-research.-results-confirmed-that-current-llms-do-not-exhibit-uniform-knowledge-across-academic-fields-and-that-meaningful-performance-differences-exist-between-models.-these-findings-reinforce-the-need-for-field-level-evaluation-and-informed-model-selection.-the-studys-contributions-lay-the-groundwork-for-more-transparent-rigorous-and-domain-aware-assessment-of-large-language-models.-the-dissertation-now-concludes-with-a-consolidated-understanding-of-llm-knowledge-variability-and-its-implications-for-research-education-and-practice.}{%
\section*{This chapter interpreted the study\textquotesingle s findings,
addressed its limitations, and articulated its implications,
contributions, and recommendations for future research. Results
confirmed that current LLMs do not exhibit uniform knowledge across
academic fields and that meaningful performance differences exist
between models. These findings reinforce the need for field-level
evaluation and informed model selection. The study's contributions lay
the groundwork for more transparent, rigorous, and domain-aware
assessment of large language models. The dissertation now concludes with
a consolidated understanding of LLM knowledge variability and its
implications for research, education, and
practice.}\label{this-chapter-interpreted-the-studys-findings-addressed-its-limitations-and-articulated-its-implications-contributions-and-recommendations-for-future-research.-results-confirmed-that-current-llms-do-not-exhibit-uniform-knowledge-across-academic-fields-and-that-meaningful-performance-differences-exist-between-models.-these-findings-reinforce-the-need-for-field-level-evaluation-and-informed-model-selection.-the-studys-contributions-lay-the-groundwork-for-more-transparent-rigorous-and-domain-aware-assessment-of-large-language-models.-the-dissertation-now-concludes-with-a-consolidated-understanding-of-llm-knowledge-variability-and-its-implications-for-research-education-and-practice.}}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{This chapter interpreted the
study\textquotesingle s findings, addressed its limitations, and
articulated its implications, contributions, and recommendations for
future research. Results confirmed that current LLMs do not exhibit
uniform knowledge across academic fields and that meaningful performance
differences exist between models. These findings reinforce the need for
field-level evaluation and informed model selection. The study's
contributions lay the groundwork for more transparent, rigorous, and
domain-aware assessment of large language models. The dissertation now
concludes with a consolidated understanding of LLM knowledge variability
and its implications for research, education, and practice.}

